1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Welcome to Gullim — "Investment records become lifelong assets." Click "Start" and select "Continue with Google" to sign in.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:14,000
Select your Google account. A warning appears because the app is pending verification. Click "Advanced" then "Go to gulim.co.kr" to proceed.

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Gullim requests access to Google Drive and Google Sheets. These permissions allow the app to read and write your investment data. Check the boxes and click "Continue" to grant access.

4
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Welcome screen appears. Click "Select from Google Drive" to connect your spreadsheet. Use the file picker to search and select your investment record sheet.

5
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Dashboard loads with data pulled directly from your Google Sheet. View total assets (33.7M KRW), profit/loss, and daily balance trend graph.

6
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Navigate to the "History" tab. View monthly transaction summaries including dividends, deposits, and withdrawals — all synced from your spreadsheet.

7
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Add a new record manually. Click the pencil icon, select "Manual Input," enter date (2025.12.15), stock name, and dividend amount (100,000 KRW).

8
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Save the entry. "Dividend history saved" confirms success. This data is written directly to your Google Spreadsheet in real-time.

9
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Switch to the "Portfolio" tab. View your holdings, current valuations, return rates, and portfolio weights — all fetched from your spreadsheet.

10
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Go to "Settings" and select "Sheet Connection Management" to change the linked spreadsheet.

11
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Select "Change to another sheet," paste a new Google Sheet URL, and click "Change." You control which file Gullim can access.

12
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Dashboard reloads with the new sheet data. Total assets now show 60.9M KRW with +128.2% return. All your data stays in YOUR Google Drive.

